<SLUG> BC-DOWD-COLUMN-1STLD-WRITETHRU-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
COMMENTARY: NEVER ON SUNDAY, MONDAY OR ... 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Subs 5th and 18th grafs for wording changes)  By MAUREEN DOWD   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ We're trapped in the windmills of her mind.
</P>
<P>
   The resolution of the Elian case hinges on Janet Reno's inner
conflicts, her Waco flashbacks, and her post-traumatic-stress
syndrome from the Miami riots during her time as prosecutor there.
</P>
<P>
   In Waco, she gave in to her macho FBI guys and moved too soon,
too forcefully. So in Miami, she calls the shots and doesn't move
at all.
</P>
<P>
   The harder the attorney general tries to come to the rescue, the
more elusive the rescue becomes. The more compassionate she is, the
more endangered the object of her compassion. The tougher she
talks, the deeper the other side digs in.
</P>
<P>
   You can feel her loneliness. She's the president's least
favorite Cabinet member, charged with trying to enforce the law in
an administration that so artfully skirts it.
</P>
<P>
   As in Waco, Bill Clinton is ducking behind the tall gal. He
could end the Elian muddle by simply picking up the phone. Instead
of partying and panhandling in Hollywood, he could grab the chance
to lead.
</P>
<P>
   The first lady casts herself as a defender of children. But
she's too busy actualizing her self-worth in New York to worry
about a real child's psyche being razed by a vengeful village.
</P>
<P>
   Now that Al Gore has outpandered even himself, he's lost
interest.
</P>
<P>
   Reno gets easily intimidated by worst-case scenarios. Highlight
reels of her disasters play in her head in an endless loop,
negating every option.
</P>
<P>
   She does not want to take Elian out of the house at night
because it would look heavy-handed. She does not want to take Elian
during the day or on weekends because the crowds would be too
boisterous. She does not want to take him in the rain, because he
would get wet. She does not want to take Elian at Miami's rush
hour, Marisleysis' medication hour or Uncle Lazaro's happy hour.
</P>
<P>
   She did not want to take Elian over Thanksgiving or Christmas.
Or in January because she was hoping his Cuban grandmothers could
reclaim him. Or in February because she wanted to let the Miami
relatives have their day in court.
</P>
<P>
   She did not want to take Elian in March because the Little
Havana crowds were getting unruly and she did not want to provoke
another riot. Even when Lazaro gave Diane Sawyer temporary custody
of Elian, Reno resisted the notion that the uncle might be
exploiting the boy.
</P>
<P>
   She did not want to take Elian in early April, because she
assumed Lazaro would hand the 6-year-old over voluntarily to his
father.
</P>
<P>
   She did not want to take Elian last Wednesday night, when she
met with the boy and his relatives at the nun's house in Miami
Beach, because she had given her word that she would wait for a
negotiated solution.
</P>
<P>
   She did not want to take Elian on Thursday, after the relatives
broke their word and scorned the 2 p.m. federal deadline to turn
him over, because she wanted the scofflaws to have another day in
court.
</P>
<P>
   She did not want to take Elian in the furious aftermath of the
coco loco family giving TV the ``Papa don't preach'' videotape _
widely deemed abusive _ because she said she never saw the tape.
</P>
<P>
   She did not want to take Elian on Sunday, after lawyers for the
Miami relatives demonized the boy's father with unsubstantiated
smears, because she was still waiting for the appeals court
decision.
</P>
<P>
   She did not want to take Elian after ``60 Minutes,'' on which
Dan Rather gave the father a ``man-to-man'' challenge to weep over
the hostage videotape, because she was Still Waiting.
</P>
<P>
   She did not want to take Elian on Tuesday, after a pediatrician
engaged by the INS warned her in a letter that ``Elian Gonzalez is
now in a state of imminent danger to his physical and emotional
well-being in a home that I consider to be psychologically
abusive,'' because she thought the situation was too confused.
</P>
<P>
   She does not want to take Elian this week because there was some
bad karma attached to the anniversaries of Waco, the Bay of Pigs,
Oklahoma City and Columbine.
</P>
<P>
   She does not want to take Elian on Sunday because it's Easter.
Then comes Earth Day, Arbor Day, the NBA playoffs and Cinco de
Mayo.
</P>
<P>
   Perhaps Father's Day. Weather permitting. (BOX)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
