Kansas anymore. For more than a decade, three of the founding
members of progressive-rock group Kansas have called Atlanta home.
As the band prepares a new album and reunion tour - kicking off
Friday at the Frederick Brown Jr. Amphitheater - we spend some time
with the original wayward sons to talk about the new record and why
Atlanta is home. (Tate, Atlanta Journal-Constitution),
