 For Immediate Release  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Boston Globe plans to move the following FEATURE stories for
use by NYTimes News Service clients.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; For questions about stories, please contact  &UR; Frank Perrotta
 &LR; at the Boston Globe,  &UR; 617-929-2597. &LR;  For individual purchase of
graphics or photos please call  &UR; 888-346-9867  &LR; or  &UR; 888-603-1036 &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   All stories will bear the BOS designator.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   CANADA-GRIZZLY (Montreal) _ United States, Canada are entering a
new battleground involving grizzlies. Animal rights groups in
Canada are opposing an effort to transplant the big bears in
wilderness Idaho and Montana. By Colin Nickerson. &UR;  &LR; 1335 words.
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-JUDGE (Moscow) _ In Russia, where courts convict 99.5
percent of all criminal defendants, one judge is calling for reform
of a one-sided system that assumes guilt unless proven innocent. By
Brian Whitmore. 1200 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   JUROR-COUNSELING (Boston) _ For years, jurors have been
subjected to horrific murder and rape trials and then sent home
with nothing more than a ``thank you'' for doing their civic duty.
Now some court officials say jurors should be offered mental health
counseling. By Ralph Ranalli. 880 words.
</P>
<P>
   PASSOVER-MATZO (Boston) _ As Jews prepare begin celebrating
Passover, the consumption of hand-made matzo, the unleavened bread
central to the observance, is experiencing a revival. And it is
rekindling a century-old debate over the manufacture of matzo. By
Michael Paulson. 1500 words. PHOTO
</P>
<P>
   FINDING-KIDD (Provincetown, Mass.) _ Treasure hunter Barry
Clifford is about to return to Madagascar for the Discovery Channel
to confirm he has found the wreck of Capt. Kidd's pirate ship. By
David Arnold. 1360 words. PHOTO
</P>
<P>
   TALL-DESCENDANTS (Beals Island, Maine) _ Tall Barney Beal was 6
feet 10 and strong enough to kill a horse with a punch to the head.
Now, in the world of Down East basketball, eight players on the
championship-winning girls' team _ are direct descendents. By Ellen
Barry. 1320 words.
</P>
