</P>
<P>
   VT-GAY-MARRIAGE (Montpelier, Vt.) _ The bill creating the
closest thing this country has to gay marriage passed out of the
Vermont Senate Wednesday, and must jump only a last hurdle in the
House before it goes to the governor, who says he will sign it.
Many lawmakers who voted for it did so despite hate mail and calls
from constituents and from indications that they are sealing their
political death warrants. By Carey Goldberg.
</P>
<P>
   OKLA-BOMB-ANNIVERSARY (Oklahoma City) _  &UR;  &LR; The city and the
president remember the federal building bombing, mourn the dead and
celebrate the healing. By Marc Lacey.
</P>
<P>
   MCCAIN-SC-FLAG (Columbia, S.C.) _ John McCain returns to South
Carolina and makes clear his views on the Confederate battle flag,
an issue on which he hedged his position during the South Carolina
Republican primary. By Steven A. Holmes.
</P>
<P>
   CUBAN-BOY (Dateline to come) _ Developments in the continuing
custody battle over Elian Gonzalez. U.S. Attorney General Janet
Reno said Wednesday that she would not rule out the forcible
removal of Elian from his Miami relatives.
</P>
<P>
   CALIF-MARIJUANA (Santa Cruz, Calif.) _ Santa Cruz voters
approved the medical use of marijuana without the supervision of a
physician, effective Wednesday. By Evelyn Nieves.
</P>
<P>
   TENN-EXECUTION (Nashville, Tenn.) _ With 100 people holding
vigil, Tennessee executed child killer Robert Glen Coe by injection
Wednesday morning. He was the first person to be put to death in
the state in 40 years. By Emily Yellin.
</P>
<P>
   SCI-FIBER-CANCER (Undated) _ Two large and rigorous studies
involving thousands of people have failed to confirm one of the
most widely held beliefs about diet and health _ that eating low
fat, high fiber foods can protect against colon cancer. By Gina
Kolata.
</P>
