F. Kennedy was president, the symbol of U. S.-Cuban relations was
an array of Soviet-made missiles capable of firing deadly nuclear
warheads into our country. Now the symbol a six-year-old boy named
Elian Gonzalez, whose custody has triggered a bitter dispute
between Cuban Americans in Miami and the residents of Fidel
Castro's island domain. By ROBERT E. THOMPSON.
