<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   CANADA-GRIZZLY (Montreal) _ United States, Canada are entering a
new battleground involving grizzlies. Animal rights groups in
Canada are opposing an effort to transplant the big bears in
wilderness Idaho and Montana. By Colin Nickerson. &UR;  &LR; 1335 words.
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-JUDGE (Moscow) _ In Russia, where courts convict 99.5
percent of all criminal defendants, one judge is calling for reform
of a one-sided system that assumes guilt unless proven innocent. By
Brian Whitmore. 1200 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   JUROR-COUNSELING (Boston) _ For years, jurors have been
subjected to horrific murder and rape trials and then sent home
with nothing more than a ``thank you'' for doing their civic duty.
Now some court officials say jurors should be offered mental health
counseling. By Ralph Ranalli. 880 words.
</P>
<P>
