that in the rest of the nation.
</P>
<P>
   In 1994, Safelite CFO Douglas Herron asked Hamilton how the
company could improve its plan. Hamilton had a few ideas.
</P>
<P>
   To spur participation, Safelite started automatically enrolling
new employees in the plan unless they specifically opted out of it.
And to reward job longevity, the company started matching 20
