<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Locate hard to find items
 &HT;    By Marylin Johnson
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Having trouble finding a particular item? We'll try to help you
locate it. But because of the volume of mail, we cannot track down
every request. Readers whose queries are answered in the column
will receive a blue-and-cream canvas Buyer's Edge tote bag. Write
us at Buyer's Edge Find It,The Atlanta Journal-Constitution, P.O.
Box 4689, Atlanta, GA 30302; e-mail us at buyersedge(at)ajc.com
(please include your name, the city you live in and daytime phone
number); or call 404-582-7642.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I moved from Pennsylvania to Georgia and have been unable to
find Cope's canned corn locally. I want to make their recipe Baked
Corn, which is absolutely delicious. Can you help?
</P>
<P>
   _ Avis L. Rhodes, Marietta, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: You can get ``corny'' with this sweet perennial veggie. For a
hundred years, the Cope family has been growing sweet corn in
Pennsylvania Dutch country. Unfortunately, the company does not
sell its products locally. These include white or golden evaporated
sweet corn in cans (ready to heat and serve) or toasted dried sweet
corn, which either must be ground in a blender or soaked in a
liquid before cooking. However, you can order Cope products on
their Web site at www.copefoods.com. Or order them by calling
1-800-745-8211. Three 7.5-ounce cartons of dried sweet corn are
$11.65; six cans of the evaporated golden sweet corn are $12.90.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I am looking for Jaffa Cakes, made by McVitie's, an English
company. My sister sends them to me from Norway.
</P>
<P>
   _ Terry Wills,
</P>
<P>
   Alpharetta, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: No need to have sis send those sweets anymore. We found your
Jaffa Cakes _ made in Britain _ at Harry's Farmers Market, 2025
Satellite Pointe, Duluth (770-416-6900). A box of 12 cakes is
$2.19. To our eyes, these light little sponge goodies, with a hint
of orange, look more like cookies iced in chocolate than cakes.
They would be delicious served with ice cream or eaten with a cuppa
Joe.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I am having trouble finding Old English Scratch Cover for
light woods.
</P>
<P>
   _ Mima Carmichael,
</P>
<P>
   Acworth, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: We scratched our heads and came up with your product at
Lowe's Home Improvement Warehouse, 4855 Stone Mountain Highway,
Lilburn (770-978-9724). An 8-ounce bottle is $3.67. Scratch Cover,
says manufacturer Reckitt &AMP; Benckiser, hides scratches and nicks
and helps restore damaged wood surfaces. This product is formulated
to work on light to medium woods such as pine and oak. You can also
order this product directly from the company (an 8-ounce bottle is
$4.39): 1-800-456-9477.
</P>
<P>
   Q: For months, I have not been able to find Dermassage
Dishwashing Liquid. I fear they have quit making it. If not, I
would love to know where I could purchase it. My hands would really
thank you.
</P>
<P>
   _ Hope
</P>
<P>
   Sorrells,
</P>
<P>
   Tucker, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: Fear not. Your favorite dishwashing liquid is available at
Ingles Supermarket, 4815 Rockbridge Road, Stone Mountain
(404-299-0698). A 22-ounce bottle is 99 cents. This liquid, says
manufacturer Colgate-Palmolive, is phosphate free, and
dermatologist tested. And your hands are welcome.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I once complimented a woman on her perfume, which smelled
heavenly. She said it received mention in the movie ``Scent of a
Woman.'' I think in the film, the character played by Al Pacino
said the perfume was Fleurs de Rocaille. Five years later, I still
haven't been able to find this perfume. I've searched everywhere,
including the Internet. Can you please help me?
</P>
<P>
   _ Rebekah A. Hall, Atlanta
</P>
<P>
   A: We nosed around a bit and came up with your fragrance; in
fact, two versions. Fleurs de Rocaille (translated flowers of the
rock) by Caron came out in 1933. It's a blend of rose, jasmine,
carnation and oakmoss. This indeed is the one mentioned in the
movie ``Scent of a Woman.'' In 1983, Caron introduced Fleur de
Rocaille, without the ``s'' on Fleur, in tribute to the fragrance's
50th anniversay. This one is lighter, a fruity floral containing
gardenia notes, jasmine, rose, lily of the valley and wood notes.
Saks Fifth Avenue in Phipps Plaza (404-261-7234) carries both
versions. A 1.7-ounce eau de toilette of each version is $60. You
can also order this fragrance through the Caron Boutique, 675
Madison Ave., New York, NY 10021, 212-319-4888.
</P>
<P>
   _Contributing: Michelle C. Brooks
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
