for first-quarter earnings, thanks in part to soaring prices in the
company's pulp and paper business. Georgia-Pacific Group, which
excludes the Atlanta-based company's timber business, said today
that first-quarter profit nearly doubled to $194 million, or $1.11
a share, compared with year-ago profit of $99 million, or 56 cents
a share. Georgia-Pacific Group was expected to earn $1.02 a share,
based on a survey of analysts by First Call. (Bond, Atlanta
Joujrnal-Constitution). 12.
