<HEADER>
A1566 &Cx1f; ttj-z
r k BC-SALTER-COLUMN-HNS &LR;      04-19 0642
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SALTER-COLUMN-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;     HOW TO SIGN UP FOR THE MIAMI CIVIL DISOBEDIENCE SCHOOL 
</HEADLINE>
   &HT;     (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 &HT;     By STEPHANIE SALTER  
 &HT;     c.2000 San Francisco Examiner  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN FRANCISCO _ Are you ticked off at the federal government for
anything? Hate paying all those taxes, for instance? Think NASA is
a big waste of time and money? Maybe you just liked the way Old
Glory looked with 48 stars and want to rescind Alaska's and
Hawaii's statehood.
</P>
<P>
   Have we got the solution for you.
</P>
<P>
   Call the 800 number now scrolling across your screen and find
out where the nearest Elian's Miami Relatives School of Civil
Disobedience is located in your area.
</P>
<P>
   Forget everything you ever learned in U.S. government class in
high school. Forget the old Jimmy Stewart movies. Forget what the
cops and judges tell you.
</P>
<P>
   FORGET THE LAW!
</P>
<P>
   As Elian Gonzalez's Miami relatives have proven, this is the
United States of America in 2000, and it's a whole new ballgame.
Let THEM show you how to play to win!
</P>
<P>
   Voiceover and video of Elian's great-uncle Lazaro Gonzalez,
standing before a wall of TV cameras, klieg lights and reporters.
</P>
<P>
   LG: ``Hello! You know my name, you know my face, and by now, you
know I don't take anything from anybody. Especially the U.S.
government.
</P>
<P>
   ``You got a beef with the Immigration and Naturalization
Service? Had it up to here with the decisions those jack-booted
municipal, state and federal judges keep handing down? Sick and
tired of hearing Janet Reno talk about anything?
</P>
<P>
   ``Come sign up for a weekend seminar at Elian's Miami Relatives
School of Civil Disobedience. That's right. In just two days of
classes and workshops, you can learn everything we've learned since
Thanksgiving about doing what you damn well please while the mighty
U.S. government stands around with its finger up its nose.''
</P>
<P>
   Voiceover and video of Elian's cousin Marisleysis Gonzalez,
taking her own blood pressure and pulse then falling into a swoon
on an overstuffed sofa.
</P>
<P>
   MG: ``Do I look stressed out? In need of a hospital bed and an
IV drip of sedatives? Maybe I am, and maybe I'm not.
</P>
<P>
   ``At the Elian's Miami Relatives School of Civil Disobedience
you can learn this effective, time-buying technique and many, many
others. Never again will you have to quake at a deadline, court
order or even a request from the president of the United States. In
the finest American tradition of the Boston Tea Party, we will show
you how to spit in the face of authority and make sure there are
350 television cameras rolling when you do it.
</P>
<P>
   ``In just one weekend, you can learn how to attract support from
every pocket of influence in your community. Need a high-ranking
Roman Catholic nun to give you her seal of approval? We'll show you
how. Always wanted a movie star or pop singer on your side? Once
you pick up a few basic skills, it's as easy as 1-2-3.
</P>
<P>
   ``As for politicians _ Uncle Lazaro and I can show you enough in
one workshop to get half of Congress eating out of your hand.''
</P>
<P>
   Video montage of 38 different speeches in which President
Clinton and Attorney General Reno say firmly, ``The boy belongs
with his father; he MUST be returned now.'' The announcer's
voiceover:
</P>
<P>
   ``Admit it _ ever since Elian washed up on the Florida shore,
haven't you been mystified and wondered, `How in the hell do his
relatives in Miami get away with this stuff?'
</P>
<P>
   ``Well, the answer to that mystery _ and the ticket to a freedom
you have never known _ waits just behind the doors of any Elian's
Miami Relatives School of Civil Disobedience.
</P>
<P>
   ``What are you waiting for? You want to be some law-abiding
chump for the rest of your life? Call that 800 number now. We take
Visa, MasterCard, Discover, American Express and Diners. We can
arrange easy payments. Operators are standing by.''
</P>
</TEXT>
