 &HT;    With GORE-GUNS.
 &HT;    c.2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   GORE VS. BUSH ON GUN CONTROL
</P>
<P>
   Vice President Al Gore favors:
</P>
<P>
   _ Mandatory photo ID licenses for handgun buyers.
</P>
<P>
   _ Banning cheap ``junk'' guns, so-called ``Saturday night
specials.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Banning firearms from places of worship and school events.
</P>
<P>
   _ Limiting handgun purchases to one a month.
</P>
<P>
   _ A three-day waiting period for purchases at gun shows.
</P>
<P>
   _ Requiring gun manufacturers and federally licensed sellers to
report gun sales to a state authority.
</P>
<P>
   _ Increasing penalties for gun-related crimes.
</P>
<P>
   _ Mandatory child-safety locks.
</P>
<P>
   Gov. George W. Bush of Texas favors:
</P>
<P>
   _ Aggressive enforcement of existing gun laws.
</P>
<P>
   _ Raising the minimum age for handgun possession from 18 to 21.
</P>
<P>
   _ A ban on the importation of foreign-made ``high-capacity''
ammunition clips.
</P>
<P>
   _ Instant background checks on gun show purchases.
</P>
<P>
   _ Voluntary child-safety locks.
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
