r v BC-TEXBUDGET-TEX     04-19 0292
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TEXBUDGET-TEX </SLUG>
 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Fort Worth Star-Telegram plans to move the following stories
for clients of the NYTimes News Service for AMs and PMs of
Thursday, April 18, and thereafter. If you have any questions,
please call Lou Hudson, Tom Uhler or Jim Peipert on the
Star-Telegram's National/Foreign Desk at (817) 390-7785. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   F O O D A N D D I N I N G &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FOOD-CHAPMAN-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ The whole idea of a Renaissance festival is to enjoy
the pleasures of the 16th century, but I'm not convinced those were
great times _ plagues, armadas, big bloody wars and things like
that. So the food is the main thing for me at festivals like
Scarborough Faire, in Waxahachie, south of Dallas. By ART CHAPMAN.
Story has moved in ``d'' food and dining category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
