<SLUG> BC-KENNEDY-SECURITY-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SECURITY GUARD IN KENNEDY CASE HAS RECORD, DOCUMENTS SHOW 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By ANNE E. KORNBLUT  
 c.2000 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ A female security guard who accused Representative
Patrick J. Kennedy of assaulting her in Los Angeles International
Airport has a four-decade history of arrests herself, including
cocaine and theft charges, according to court documents.
</P>
<P>
   Della Patton, 58, also appears to have used more than one fake
name, a history that could be used to undercut her credibility if
she chooses to file a civil complaint against Kennedy, whom she
said injured her arm during the altercation on March 26, a source
familiar with the case said.
</P>
<P>
   Kennedy, a Rhode Island Democrat, has admitted that he acted
rudely toward Patton, brusquely showing his identification and
demanding to pass through airport security even though he was
carrying an oversized bag. But he rebuts allegations that he
physically harmed her.
</P>
<P>
   Patton, however, insists Kennedy grabbed and shoved her when she
tried to enforce standard airport regulations and that the
altercation rendered her incapable of continuing work. She is
collecting worker's compensation and is on paid leave from her job.
News of the confrontation became public when Patton told her story
to the National Enquirer earlier this month. Neither a criminal nor
civil charge against Kennedy has been filed.
</P>
<P>
   Patton's lawyer, Paul D. Trump, rebutted reports that he had
sought a financial settlement for his client. ``That wasn't the
case,'' Trump said of earlier accounts that he phoned Kennedy's
Washington lawyer, Abbe D. Lowell, to demand a sum. ``That's
Washington capitalism, Democrat politics. . . . I don't know where
everybody gets their news.''
</P>
<P>
   Of his client's past scrapes with the law, Trump said, ``I don't
know anything about that.'' Trump said he began representing Patton
only at the time of her altercation with Kennedy.
</P>
<P>
   According to California court papers, Patton has pleaded guilty
to petty theft and cocaine possession charges and has a history of
susbtance abuse. In addition to two married names, she also appears
to have gone by at least two aliases, Vessie Carter and Vessie
Truitt.
</P>
<P>
   Kennedy declined to comment.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-04-19-00 1903EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
