of apartheid is the growing confidence and increased prosperity of
wealthy Afrikaners under black rule. Even in a country of countless
ironies, this development may someday be listed among the more
notable. After all, the Afrikaners, who are descended from Dutch,
German and French settlers, invented the brutal system of racial
segregation known as apartheid. By Rachel L. Swarns.
