<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Coke names senior VP, other executives
 &HT;    By Christopher Seward
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Coca-Cola elevated Ingrid Saunders Jones, one of its
top African-American executives, to senior vice president and
promoted several other executives to vice president.
</P>
<P>
   In an announcement Wednesday, Chairman Doug Daft said the
promotions ``demonstrate the importance we place on commitments we
have made at the Coca-Cola Co. _ specifically our commitment to
maintaining productive relationships with the communities where we
do business and our commitment to provide our consumers with
products of the very highest quality.''
</P>
<P>
   Jones was promoted to senior vice president, corporate external
affairs. She had been vice president since 1991. Previously she
held executive roles in urban affairs.
</P>
<P>
   Coca-Cola also announced the following promotions:
</P>
<P>
   _ Carlton Curtis was named vice president, executive assistant
to the president and chief operating officer. He has held positions
in corporate public relations, the technical and administrative
divisions, media relations and education marketing, among other
areas.
</P>
<P>
   _ Rudy M. Beserra was elected vice president, corporate Latin
affairs. He was named director of corporate Latin affairs in 1993
and was made an assistant vice president of the company a year
later.
</P>
<P>
   _ Coretha Rushing was named vice president of human resources.
She was most recently executive assistant to the executive vice
president of operations support.
</P>
<P>
   _ Patricia Powell was named vice president, technical division,
a newly created division she was named to head in March. Powell was
formerly a vice president of Coca-Cola North America.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
