Or had the young heir been spirited away from harm after his
parents were sent to the guillotine? On Wednesday, two scientists
said they had proof that the boy was indeed 10-year-old Louis XVII.
After examining all that remains of the boy - a dried heart - they
were able to match the boy's DNA with that of other members of the
royal family. (Library of Congress/The New York Times)
