A1872 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r s BC-FBN-COWBOYS-PEETE-TEX     04-19 0493
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-COWBOYS-PEETE-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>


</HEADLINE>
 
COWBOYS INTERESTED IN RODNEY PEETE (For use by NYTimes News Service
clients) 
By RAY BUCK 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVING, Texas _ The Cowboys are showing an interest in recently
released Washington Redskins quarterback Rodney Peete, although
owner Jerry Jones said yesterday that the team will take a
wait-and-see attitude toward the 11-year veteran's availability
until after the April 28-30 minicamp.
</P>
<P>
   The Cowboys need to see how the pecking order behind Troy Aikman
shakes out. This minicamp will mark the first time coaches will get
a chance to see 31-year-old quarterback Paul Justin, who was signed
as an unrestricted free agent from the St. Louis Rams last month.
</P>
<P>
   ``We'll sure take a look at \R Peete\S,'' said Stephen Jones,
Cowboys' director of player personnel. ``We had him before \R1994\S
and really liked him then. Our coaches will continue to evaluate
him and see if he could be a fit here or not.''
</P>
<P>
   Peete, 34, hasn't been a full-time starter since tearing the
patella tendon in his right knee in Week 5 of the 1996 season with
Philadelphia. He has been mostly a backup each of the past three
seasons with the Eagles (1997-98) and Redskins (1999).
</P>
<P>
   When the Redskins signed Jeff George to back up starter Brad
Johnson, Peete became expendable and was released on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   Justin, who has had 10 starts in five NFL seasons with three
teams, is considered the favorite to win the Cowboys' No. 2 job
because of his experience.
</P>
<P>
   But the Cowboys will keep an eye on the situation because Peete,
who backed up Aikman in '94 (appearing in seven games with one
start) knows the offense that offensive coordinator Jack Reilly and
pass-offense consultant Ernie Zampese are bringing back to the
Cowboys this season.
</P>
<P>
   If the Cowboys pursue Peete, it would probably be for the
$440,000 league minimum for a veteran.
</P>
<P>
   Peete's agent, Tom Condon, could not be reached for
comment.Star-Telegram yesterday.]
</P>
<P>
   In his NFL career, Peete has thrown for 13,686 yards and 61
touchdowns (compared with Justin's 2,614 yards and eight TDs).
Peete originally was drafted by Detroit, where he was a starter
most of his five seasons with the Lions.
</P>
<P>
   Mike Quinn, 26, will be given a chance to compete with Justin
for the Cowboys' No. 2 QB job. Quinn, who has no NFL starts in
three seasons, held the No. 3 job last season although he didn't
appear in any games.
</P>
<P>
   Jason Garrett, Aikman's longtime backup, defected to the New
York Giants in February via unrestricted free agency, leaving the
Cowboys without a seasoned No. 2 quarterback prior to their signing
Justin. \Nsubheds:Free agents sign The Cowboys signed three more
undrafted rookie free agents yesterday, bringing the total to 17 in
three days. They are Alabama State wide receiver Damon Hodge, who
is 6-foot-1 with 4.5-second speed in the 40; Troy State defensive
end Aaron Fields, 6-4, 243 pounds; and Utah State punter Micah
Knorr.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
